annotationA: Protein disulfide-isomerase A6 homolog; Calcium-binding protein 1 (CaBP1) resides in the lumen of the endoplasmic reticulum. CaBP1 seems to be relocated outside cells during apoptosis and involved in the phagocytosis of apoptotic cells
annotationB: Signal peptidase complex catalytic subunit SEC11; Peptidase activity; serine-type peptidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: signal peptide processing
